# plcproj File Rules

The `.plcproj` is an MSBuild XML file that registers all PLC source files.

## Register a New File

Add inside an `<ItemGroup>` block:

```xml
<Compile Include="POUs\FB_NewDevice.TcPOU">
  <SubType>Code</SubType>
</Compile>

<Compile Include="DUTs\ST_NewDevice_Data.TcDUT">
  <SubType>Code</SubType>
</Compile>

<Compile Include="GVLs\GVL_NewDomain.TcGVL">
  <SubType>Code</SubType>
</Compile>
```

## Register a New Folder

Add inside the `<ItemGroup>` that contains `<Folder>` elements:

```xml
<Folder Include="POUs\NewSubfolder" />
```

## Library References

Placeholder (version-independent):
```xml
<PlaceholderReference Include="Tc3_JsonXml">
  <DefaultResolution>Tc3_JsonXml, * (Beckhoff Automation GmbH)</DefaultResolution>
  <Namespace>Tc3_JsonXml</Namespace>
</PlaceholderReference>
```

## Critical Rules

- **Path separators**: Use backslashes `\` in `Include` attributes (Windows convention)
- **Always add `<SubType>Code</SubType>`** for Compile items
- **Methods are NOT registered separately** - only the parent .TcPOU file
- **Match the actual file path** on disk exactly (case-sensitive in some builds)
- **Do not duplicate** entries - check if file is already registered before adding
